Text: This week it has been difficult to herd cats which has meant we have not been able to achieve our goals for the week.
We have had trouble getting in touch with Rodney, the project founder and eliciting valuable information as there has been a direction change in the objectives of the project.
With the support from Teacher2 and Teacher1, we have decided to continue with the original project direction as the new proposed project is not feasible to accomplish in 2 short weeks.
Rodney has assured us that by the end of the week, we will have the information our group requires to continue ahead.
With that information being promised to us, and the weekend ahead of interviewing students and teachers, we should be on track to begin technical development early next week.
I am looking forward to this, although I do feel I have significant gaps in my knowledge to be able to hit the ground running.
Roro has kindly taken onboard the role of teaching myself and Toto the database applications and the apps.
We will need a session early next week to ensure all team members are up-to-date with what needs to happen.

I believe that after sitting down for a few hours and beginning work on the project's technical aspects, we will all feel a lot more confident in what needs to be done and have the confidence to work independently.
Our team's availability has worked well.
When needing advice or discussion, we are all more than happy to make time.
What has not been working well has been the founders being extremely busy this past week, meaning we did not have a chance to catch up with him until the end of the week.
This was when he notified us of some project direction changes which we will not be able to do.

We still believe there is a lot of value for us to execute this project and add value to our client with the original direction and if this week were to happen again, we would definitely as a group make more decisions on our clients behalf and rely less on their communication.
This is also a goal for next week, to push through and rely on each other more for the project direction.
